               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝṣṣǝw, Lectionary for the entire year (fols. 3ra-91vb)
                     I-1) Scriptural readings with Psalms for liturgical periods, fasts and feasts
                     (for the entire year) (fols. 3ra-40rb; 59ra-91vb)
 - Liturgical period
                     called Yoḥannǝs: fols. 3ra-6ra
 - Feasts of the Minor Prophets (Näbiyat
                     Ṣadǝqan): fols. 6ra-8rb
 - Liturgical period Masqal: fols. 8rb-11ra
 -
                     Liturgical period Ṣǝge: fols. 11ra-12va, 14ra-16vb
 - Liturgical period
                     Sǝbkät: fols. 12va-14ra
 - Liturgical period Lǝdät: fols. 16vb-19rb
 -
                     Feast of the Epiphany (Ṭǝmqät): fols. 19rb-21ra
 - Feast of the Wedding of
                     Cana (Qana za-Gälila): fols. 21ra-22vb
 - Feasts of Mary (za-ʾǝgziʾtǝnä):
                     fols. 22vb-26rb
 - Feasts of the Martyrs (Samāʿtāt): fols. 26rb-28va
 -
                     Feasts of the Righteous Ones (Ṣadǝqan): fols. 28va-31vb
 - Fast of the
                     Apostles (Ḥawāryāt): fols. 31vb-36ra
 - Feats of Angels (Mälaʾǝkt): fols.
                     36ra-40rb
 - Incarnation (Mäggäbit 29): fols. 59ra-60ra
 -
                     Transfiguration (Dabra Tabor): fols. 60ra-62va
 - 8th Sunday before Easter,
                     Sunday of “He who descended…” (za-wärädä…) or “of the Encounter with the Fast”
                     (Qäbbäla ṣom): fols. 62va-65va
 - 7th Sunday before Easter, Sunday “of the
                     Holy” (Qǝddǝst): fols. 65va-67vb
 - 4th Sunday before Easter, Sunday “of
                     the Mount of Olives” (Dabra Zäyt): fols. 67vb-70va
 - 3rd Sunday before
                     Easter, Sunday “of the Good Servant” (Gǝbǝr ḫer): fols. 70va-72vb
 - Palm
                     Sunday (Hosaʿǝna): fols. 72vb-76ra
 - Maundy Thursday (Ṣalota Ḫamus): fols.
                     76ra-77vb
 - Resurrection (Tǝnśaʾe): fols. 77vb-80va
 - Sunday after
                     Easter (Fäṣṣämnä…): fols. 80va-82vb 
 - Ascension (ʿƎrgät): fols.
                     82vb-86rb
 - Pentecost (Ṗaraqliṭos): fols. 86rb-88va
 - Liturgical
                     period Kǝrämt (“Rainy season”): fols. 88va-90ra
 - Blessing prayer
                     (Bakǝkännä ʾƎgziʾo… “Bless us, Lord…): fols. 90vb-91vb
 I-2) Scriptural
                     readings for the days of the week (fols. 40rb-59ra)
 - Monday (sänuy):
                     fols. 40rb-43vb
 - Tuesday (śälus): fols. 43vb-46ra
 - Wednesday
                     (räbuʿ): fols. 46ra-48va
 - Thursday (ḥamus): fols. 48va-50rb
 - Friday
                     (ʾarb): fols. 50rb-52ra
 - Saturday (qadāmit sanbat): fols. 52ra-54vb
                     - Sunday (ʾǝḥud): fols. 54vb-59ra
 
 Additiones 1-2;
                     colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <title>Maṣḥafa gǝṣṣǝw, Lectionary for the entire year</title>
                     <note>- Text I is called Maṣḥafa gǝṣṣǝw in the incipit (s. <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus>) (cp.<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESdmd012">DMD-012</ref>).</note>
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <title>Scriptural readings with Psalms for liturgical periods, fasts and feasts
                           (for the entire year) </title>
                        <note>- Psalms are written in smaller script by hand a (e.g. <locus target="#18ra">18ra</locus>, 30va), except in <locus target="#4vb">4vb</locus>.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <title>Scriptural
                           readings for the days of the week </title>
                        
                     </msItem>
                <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#91vb">91vb</locus>: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸኒ[sic]፡ በዳኅና፡ ወበሰላም፡
                        ለኃጥእ፡ አባ፡ ገብረ፡ መድኅን፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም። Written in the main hand. The name of the
                        scribe and the donor (cp. supplication formulas, e.g. <locus target="#11vb">11vb</locus>, 19rb, 24rb) is Gabra Madḫǝn. </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  
                  
