                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, vivid red, reddish-brown.</seg>
                        The name of an
                        individual, Gabra Madḫǝn is mentioned, probably the scribe and one the
                        donors (s. Additio 2)<date>First half of 20th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors in supplication
                           formulas; incipit of Text II and its sections; titles of books and the
                           first line of readings; directives to the ministers such as qǝdmä wängel;
                           abbreviation of the directive yǝbǝl ḥǝzb, “the people say” in Text I; the
                           word salām in Text II; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of
                           Ethiopic numbers.
 On the incipit page of Texts I (fol. 3r) a few
                           lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines). In fol. 62r, a few
                           lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="3ra" to="91vb">3ra-91vb</locus>.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
