                  <provenance>
                     Name of the scribe, Gabra Madḫǝn, is
                     mentioned in the colophon and in supplication formulas throughout Text I (e.g.,
                     11vb, 19rb, 24rb). Other names appear in the supplication formulas in Text I:
                     Gabra Giyorgis (e.g. <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus>, 6ra, 9ra), ʾAmata
                     Mikāʾel (<locus target="#4ra">4ra</locus>, 7ra, 11ra), Gabra ʾIyasus (<locus target="#8va">8va</locus>, 14vb, 20rb), Rämḫa Śǝllāse (<locus target="#14ra">14ra</locus>, 16vb, 21va), ʾAmata Māryām (<locus target="#21ra">21ra</locus>, 26rb, 83rb), Walatta Mikāʾel (<locus target="#27vb">27vb</locus>).
                     
                  </provenance>
